cc:Work.dc:description: # Pressure Measurement with BMP280 The BMP280 is a sensor that measures atmospheric pressure and temperature. Atmospheric pressure at sea level is around 1000mBar, and decreases with altitude. So if you observe closely, the pressure reading from this sensor decreases even if you raise the device by 1-2 feet, or walk up a flight of stairs. In this experiment, you need to connect the BMP280 to your device using 4 wires. + 5V -> 5V socket of SEELab3/Expeyes (Power Supply) + GND -> GND (Ground) + SCL -> SCL (Clock) + SDA -> SDA (Data line) Use flexible wires, or the AUX socket on SEELab3 with a 4 wire AUX cable to make things easier Place the sensor inside a balloon, and try to inflate it. Observe the pressure rising. You can also place it inside a polythene bag, close the opening of the bag tightly to prevent leaks, and try to compress the bag . ## Pressure Vs Volume Seal the sensor inside a syringe, and observe what happens to the pressure when the syringe is compressed, thereby reducing the volume available for the gas inside it. P_1 * V_1 = P_2 * V_2
